@page "/tilegrid"


<h1>TileGrid</h1>

<p>
    The tile grid component is based on the two-dimensional CSS grid and is able to display content in tiles. 
    The tiles can be rearranged by the user. 
    The tiles can also be resized to change the way they span across the rows and columns.
</p>

<h2 id="example">Examples</h2>

    <h3>Default</h3>
    <FluentMessageBar AllowDismiss=false Intent="MessageIntent.Warning" FadeIn=false Title="Issue with dynamic spacing">
        There is an issue with the Spacing property. It doesn't work dynamically (issue with css ? with rendering ? Do I forgot something in the config ?)
    </FluentMessageBar>

    <FluentStack Style="margin-bottom: 24px;" VerticalAlignment="VerticalAlignment.Center">
        <FluentLabel>Spacing</FluentLabel>
        <FluentSlider @bind-Value="Spacing" Min="0" Max="10" Step="1" Style="max-width: 300px; margin-top: 18px;" />
    </FluentStack>

    <div style="height: 400px">
    <FluentCxTileGrid Spacing="@Spacing"
                    Style="background-color: var(--neutral-layer-3); padding: 4px"
                    Columns="5"
                    RowHeight="75px">
        <FluentCxTileGridItem>
            CS : 1 | RS : 1
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem ColumnSpan="3">
            CS : 3 | RS : 1
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem>
            CS : 1 | RS : 1
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem ColumnSpan="5" RowSpan="2">
            CS : 5 | RS : 2
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem ColumnSpan="2" RowSpan="3">
            CS : 2 | RS : 3
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem RowSpan="2">
            CS : 1 | RS : 2
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem ColumnSpan="2" RowSpan="3">
            CS : 2 | RS : 3
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>
    </FluentCxTileGrid>
    </div>

    <h3>Reorder</h3>
    <p>The Tile Grid can reorder its items.</p>

    <FluentMessageBar AllowDismiss=false FadeIn=false Intent="MessageIntent.Warning" Title="Issue with reorder">
        There is an issue with the reorder. I don't know why but in this demo, the drag and drop seems to "fail" without any reason.
        And with this "failure", the component doesn't refresh :(
        And sadly, this failure forces us to press F5 to reload the page.
    </FluentMessageBar>

    <div style="height: 400px">
    <FluentCxTileGrid Spacing="3"
                    Style="background-color: var(--neutral-layer-3); padding: 4px"
                    Columns="3"
                    RowHeight="150px"
                    CanReorder>
        <FluentCxTileGridItem Header="Header 1">
            Some data
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem Header="Header 2">
            Some chart
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem Header="Header 3">
            An another item
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem ColumnSpan="2" Header="Header 4">
            A big chart
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem ColumnSpan="2" RowSpan="2" Header="Header 5">
            An another big chart
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem RowSpan="2" Header="Header 6">
            A last big item
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>
    </FluentCxTileGrid>
    </div>

    <h3>Resize</h3>

    <p>The Tile Grid can resize its items.</p>

    <div style="height: 400px">
    <FluentCxTileGrid Spacing="3"
                    Style="background-color: var(--neutral-layer-3); padding: 4px"
                    Columns="6"
                    ColumnWidth="350px"
                    RowHeight="75px"
                    CanResize>
        <FluentCxTileGridItem>
            Item 1
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem>
            Item 2
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem>
            Item 3
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem>
            Item 4
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem>
            Item 5
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem>
            Item 6
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem ColumnSpan="2" RowSpan="2">
            Item 7
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem ColumnSpan="2" RowSpan="2">
            Item 8
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem ColumnSpan="2" RowSpan="2">
            Item 9
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>
    </FluentCxTileGrid>
    </div>

    <h3>Column & Row spans</h3>

    <p>Each item of a tile grid can have its own columnspan and rowspan.</p>

<div style="height: 400px">
    <FluentCxTileGrid Spacing="3"
                    Style="background-color: var(--neutral-layer-3); padding: 4px"
                    Columns="4"
                    ColumnWidth="350px"
                    RowHeight="75px"
                    CanResize>
        <FluentCxTileGridItem RowSpan="1" ColumnSpan="1">
            Item 1
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem ColumnSpan="3">
            Item 2
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem ColumnSpan="2">
            Item 3
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem ColumnSpan="2">
            Item 4
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem RowSpan="3">
            Item 5
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem RowSpan="4">
            Item 6
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem ColumnSpan="2" RowSpan="2">
            Item 7
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem ColumnSpan="3" RowSpan="2">
            Item 8
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem ColumnSpan="4" RowSpan="2">
            Item 9
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>
    </FluentCxTileGrid>
    </div>

    <h3>Header</h3>

    <p>An item of the tile grid can have an header. This header can be templated.</p>

<div style="height: 200px">
    <FluentCxTileGrid Spacing="3"
                    Style="background-color: var(--neutral-layer-3); padding: 4px"
                    Columns="3"
                    ColumnWidth="350px"
                    RowHeight="150px">
        <FluentCxTileGridItem Header="With header">
            Item 1
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem>
            <HeaderTemplate>
                <FluentLabel Weight="FontWeight.Bold">With a templated header</FluentLabel>
            </HeaderTemplate>
            <ChildContent>
                Item 2

            </ChildContent>
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>

        <FluentCxTileGridItem>
            Without header
        </FluentCxTileGridItem>
    </FluentCxTileGrid>
    </div>
    <h3>Dashboard</h3>

    <p>A tile grid could be very useful to create some views like dashboard or profile of an user.</p>

